geography_name:
Definitions:
(1)Conditionally Enrolled (Ce): Students Have Documentation Of At Least One Dose Of Each Required Vaccine And An Appointment Date For The Next Due Dose(S) Of The Required Vaccine(S).
(2)Up-To-Date (Utd): Students Have All The Nh School Required Vaccines For Their Age And/Or Grade.
(3)Religious Exemption (Re): A Parent Or Legal Guardian Can Object To Immunization(S) Because Of Their Religious Beliefs. They Must Provide A Signed And Notarized Form Stating That The Child Has Not Been Immunized Because Of Religious Beliefs.
(4)Medical Exemption (Me): A Physician Must Certify That Immunization Against A Particular Disease May Be Detrimental To The Child's Health. The Exemption Shall Exist Only For The Length Of Time, In The Opinion Of The Physician, Such Immunization Would Be Detrimental To The Child. An Exemption From Immunization For One Disease Shall Not Affect Other Required Immunizations.
(5)Not Up-To-Date (Nutd): Students Do Not Have All Required Immunizations Or Documentation Of All Required Vaccines And Do Not Meet Conditional Enrollment Or Exemption Criteria.
Total Number Of Schools Reporting Data To Nh Dhhs: 553
Total Number Of Schools Not Reporting Data To Nh Dhhs:  8 (2 Public, 6 Private)
Data Sources: Online Surveys Completed By New Hampshire Schools Through Novi Survey. Date Prepared: 5/13/2022
Report Contributors:
Data Prepared By:
New Hampshire Immunization Section Bureau Of Infectious Disease Control Division Of Public Health Services

Data Reflects Information Reported Between 11/15/2021 And Completed 2/18/2022.

Definitions:
(1)Up-To-Date (Utd): Students Have All The Nh School Required Vaccines For Their Age And/Or Grade.
(2)Conditionally Enrolled (Ce): Students Have Documentation Of At Least One Dose Of Each Required Vaccine And An Appointment Date For The Next Due Dose(S) Of The Required Vaccine(S).
(3)Religious Exemption (Re): A Parent Or Legal Guardian Can Object To Immunization(S) Because Of Their Religious Beliefs. They Must Provide A Signed Form Stating That The Child Has Not Been Immunized Because Of Religious Beliefs.
(4)Medical Exemption (Me): A Licensed Health Care Provider Must Certify On Letterhead, That Immunization Against A Particular Disease May Be Detrimental To The Child's Health. The Exemption Shall Exist Only For The Length Of Time, In The Opinion Of A Licensed Health Care Provider; Such Immunization Would Be Detrimental To The Child. An Exemption From Immunization For One Disease Shall Not Affect Other Required Immunizations.
(5)Not Up-To-Date (Nutd): Students Do Not Have All Required Immunizations Or Documentation Of All Required Vaccines And Do Not Meet Conditional Enrollment Or Exemption Criteria.
